I think Elder Aimilianos told this story but a man went to an old monk and asked him for guidance in his spiritual life and he gave him a specific routine, list of prayers to perform at certain times of day, etc. and the man fell into despair because it felt too overwhelming...

He kept praying the Jesus prayer whenever he remembered and slowly with the years he started praying more regularly, decades down the line he realized he was now doing all the prayers the first monk told him to but now it was natural and didn't feel like a chore... So don't panic

It's probably really worth it investing a day or two to figure out an ideal red light setup for your room and installing the chicken lamp on like a shelf pointing towards your desk chair from an angle that doesn't bother your eyes, nice distance, etc.

Also just changing your overall light environment by getting a bunch of incandescent light bulbs and switching not only the ones in your room but also bathroom, kitchen, etc. Any change that's a one time thing and benefits you perpetually is worthwhile in terms of spending time.
